ROHAN - Eomer and Elite Rider are to be mounted at all costs. This gives them their strenght bonuses. Plus if you get them with a Spear/Sword and Bow, they are pretty hard to beat. Eothain is there to put into effect your plains sites.  Nelya will help him with this... Eothain is not a major fighter, but he can fight, just give him a sword or something.<br />
<br />
FRODO - He won&#39;t see any action.  You have enough companions to rip house.  If you feel you need something Take out a Lorien Guardian or both and add Sting and E! o G!...<br />
<br />
ELVES - Archery is there to back up Eothains Gametext.  Incase you have to play to Opponents sites.  Eothain is not a major fighter, but he can fight, just give him a sword or something.<br />
Leggy is point and shoot...that is all he is there for - Lorien Swordsmen can fight as well - if you need to give &#39;em a mount and show your oppontent how the game text works in your favor.<br />
<br />
MINIONS - Still working with Nazgul - let me know what you think about this set of Shadow.  I made some minor changes from the last decks.  Lemenya in and Morgul Gates out.  Added 1 each of Black Breath and Blade Tip.<br />
**** IF anyone has a Fierce Witch-King - I am looking for one - dmail me!!!****<br />
<br />
SITES: <br />
Plains sites except two of &#39;em.  Exercise Eothains gametext to the highest possible level.<br />
YOu can change the site 1 to Westemnet Gullies (to pull out Leggy)<br />
